The narrator of the memoir that covers six years of her life. The
titleAll But My Liferefers to what the Nazis took from Gerda,
and the book covers the physical and psychological journey that begins when she
is just fifteen years olda journey that she barely survives. Throughout the
ordeal, Gerda remains hopeful about both her familys fate and her own, and she
emphasizes the positive attributes of those around her. Gerdas character is
epitomized by her brave optimism and strength in the face of the
Holocaust.Read anin-depth analysis of Gerda Weissmann Klein.